Hardware Proporties-
-----------------------
Button-
  -GPIO
  -Mode : Toggle/On/Off/pwm_increase/pwm_decrease
  -Relay no : (Which relay should be triggered)
  
Relay-
  -GPIO
  -Mode : Normal/Inverse/pwm
  -Order : (Physcial button order to show the color) [255, if order not required]
  
Light-
  -GPIO

Communication protocols
-----------------------
[MQTT topics] (/set- send message to esp ie receive on esp) (x- number, always 0 based)
/uartout
/uartin
/debug        : All debug messages when connected to mqtt
/relay/x/set  : Set relay On/Off
/relay/x      : Relay status will be published by esp on this topic

/rcfg/set  : Relay configuration setup
/bcfg/set  : Button configuration setup


Commands for- /relay/x/set
--------------------------
0- Off
1- On
2- Toggle
3- Get current staus


JSON message formats
--------------------
Relay configure-
Add a new relay
{
  "rcfg": {
    "mode": "NEW",
    "GPIO": 1,
    "type": "Inverse"
  }
}

Delete all the relays
{
  "rcfg": {
    "mode": "DELETE_ALL"
  }
}

Get all the relays
{
  "rcfg": {
    "mode": "GET_ALL"
  }
}

Get single relay
{
  "rcfg": {
    "mode": "GET_SINGLE",
    "no": 2
  }
}

Update single relay
{
  "rcfg": {
    "mode": "UPDATE",
    "GPIO": 1,
    "type": "Inverse",
    "no": 2
  }
}
